cognos-to-powerbi.skill/
│
├── SKILL.md
│   # Core brain of the skill (system prompt for Claude)
│   # Defines:
│   # - Role (Cognos → Power BI converter)
│   # - Input/Output contract
│   # - Step-by-step transformation pipeline
│   # - Strict rules (no hallucination, schema compliance)
│   # - Error handling & retry logic
│   # - Output format (model.json, report.json, errors[])
│
├── rules/
│   # Deterministic transformation logic split into focused modules
│   # Ensures consistency and reduces hallucination
│   # Example files:
│   # - dax_rules.md → Cognos expressions → DAX mappings
│   # - field_mapping.md → Cognos fields → Power BI schema
│   # - visual_mapping.md → List/Crosstab/Chart → visuals
│   # - naming_conventions.md → standard naming rules
│   # - error_handling.md → fallback and correction rules
│
├── examples/
│   # High-quality input → output pairs (few-shot learning)
│   # Teaches Claude correct transformation patterns
│   # Covers:
│   # - Simple reports (list, table)
│   # - Complex reports (crosstab, nested queries)
│   # - Edge cases (calculated fields, multiple visuals)
│   # Format: JSON with "input" (Cognos XML) and "output" (PBIP JSON)
│
├── agents/
│   # Orchestration layer (pseudo-agent workflows)
│   # Breaks conversion into explicit multi-step processes
│   # Example:
│   # - converter.md → end-to-end pipeline (parse → map → generate)
│   # - validator.md → schema + DAX validation steps
│   # - fixer.md → error correction and retry logic
│   # Enables Claude to behave like an autonomous system
│
├── assets/
│   # Reusable templates and scaffolding files
│   # Prevents invalid structure generation
│   # Example:
│   # - model.template.json → base Power BI model structure
│   # - report.template.json → report layout skeleton
│   # - pbip_structure/ → folder/file layout reference
│   # Ensures outputs are always schema-aligned
│
├── references/
│   # Authoritative documentation and schemas
│   # Used for grounding and validation
│   # Example:
│   # - pbip_schema.json → official structure reference
│   # - dax_reference.md → DAX syntax and functions
│   # - cognos_xml_guide.md → input format explanation
│   # Reduces guesswork and improves accuracy
│
├── scripts/
│   # Optional external utilities (not used directly by Claude unless MCP is enabled)
│   # Supports automation outside the model
│   # Example:
│   # - validate_pbip.py → schema validation
│   # - preprocess_xml.py → clean/normalize input
│   # - postprocess_output.py → formatting/export
│
├── evals/
│   # Testing and quality assurance layer
│   # Ensures reliability and regression safety
│   # Example:
│   # - test_cases.json → input scenarios
│   # - expected_outputs.json → correct outputs
│   # - edge_cases.json → tricky/problematic inputs
│   # Used to measure accuracy and improve the skill over time
